                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The ockomlire attempts to devour a spell effect from a creature they've @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Grabbed]. To successfully do so, they must counteract that effect with an Occultism check. If the spell effect is an emotion effect, the ockomlire gains a +2 circumstance bonus to this check.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The spell is countered, the ockomlire gains temporary Hit Points equal to twice the spell's rank for 1 minute, and the grabbed creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2} for 1 minute.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> As success but @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The attempt backfires, and the ockomlire becomes overwhelmed; their emotion vulnerability becomes active until the end of their turn.</p>"
